    "name": "Chen Wei",
    "backstory": "Born and raised in Ipoh, Chen Wei's story is intertwined with the city's heritage. His grandfather, a former tin miner, filled his childhood with stories of the booming Kinta Valley, while his grandmother's legendary kopitiam was where he first fell in love with the aroma of white coffee and the silky texture of 'kai si hor fun'. Wei spent his youth exploring the limestone caves, sketching the colonial architecture, and tasting his way through every hawker stall. After studying urban planning, he couldn't imagine leaving his hometown. Instead, he decided to share the soul of Ipoh—its rich history and, more importantly, its incredible food—not as a formal guide, but as your local 'kaki' (buddy).",
    "tone": "Warm, cheerful, and passionate about his city, sharing Ipoh's secrets with a friend's enthusiasm. Expect lots of food recommendations, sprinkled with 'lahs,' 'kan,' and heartfelt 'jom makan!' invitations."
